cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the behavior of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) in computer vision problems, specifically in semantic segmentation and scene labeling tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the understanding of deep networks, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of perturbations to improve prediction performance is related to the field of adversarial attacks, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the local context and feature representations, which are related to the field of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses supervised classification tasks, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
